What is software testing?
-- identify corrections and quality of the applictaion

How amny ways we can actually test?

--manual

--automation
When do we go for automation?
-- after manual testing passed
-- when environment is stable
-- analyze our test suite and choose our automation tools

What other automation tools do we know about ?
--Selenium, Cucumber, TestNG,UFT,QTP, Katalon Studio, Serenity

Levels of testing

-- Unit testing
-- integration testing
-- system testing
-- acceptance testing

Types of software testing?
--functional testing
 smoke test
 regression test
 sanity check

--nonfunctional testing
 Performance testing
 Security testing

What is the selenium?
Selenium is a set of tools which helps us to automate web applications >it is mainly used to perform functional testing

Selenium Components:
--Selenium IDE - integrated development environment
--Selenium RC -- Remote control
--Selenium Grid
--Selenium WebDriver

What is selenium WebDriver?
Open source automation tools wich allows you to perform actions on a web page.
WebDriver is an interface.


Advantages of Selenium WebDriver:
--Open source
--OS independent
--supports multiple languages-Ruby,Java,C#,Phyton
--works with multiple different browsers

Disadvantages of selenium WebDriver:
--cannot automate desktop applications
--no technical support
--cannot verify images/pictures
--does not have inbuilt reporting feature
--cant test  CAPTCHA/Barcodes

close() vs quit()
--close() will close the current tab
--quit() will quit the whole browser

navigate() vs get()
--get() will wait for the whole page to load whereas
 navigate() will not
 --navigate() will move back, forward, refresh
 --get() will not keep the history of your browser whereas navigate() will



